        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$\\frac{1 - \\cos(8x)}{x \\sin(4x)} = \\frac{64 \\cdot \\frac{1 - \\cos(8x)}{(8x)^2}}{4 \\cdot \\frac{\\sin(4x)}{4x}} \\cdot x \\to \\frac{64 \\cdot \\frac{1}{2}}{4 \\cdot 1} = 8$"
      },
      {
